===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}}. A tree ({{l|mul|木}}) placed upon an altar ({{l|mul|示}}), indicating a ceremony for spirit, perhaps burning sacrifical timber.

{{l|mul|奈}} and {{l|mul|祟}} were derived as variant shapes of this character.

===Etymology 1===
{{rfe|zh}}
;a kind of apple
:Attested somewhat late (e.g. in {{w|Shuowen Jiezi|SWJZ}}[https://ctext.org/shuo-wen-jie-zi/mu-bu1#n29773] & {{w|Shiming}}[https://ctext.org/shi-ming/shi-yin-shi#n40866]). {{och-l|柰|tr=nâ(t)s}} is possibly analogous to and related to {{cog|ojp|-}} {{IPAfont|nasi}} (whence {{cog|ja|梨|tr=nashi|t=pear}}) ({{zh-ref|Unger, 1983}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}})

